# Expense Splitter – Coding Rules

## Stack

- Next.js App Router
- TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS
- Shadcn UI components
- Supabase (DB + Auth)

## Structure

- `src/app/` – routes and layout
- `src/components/` – UI components (domain-specific + ui/)
- `src/lib/` – domain logic, Supabase clients, utilities

## Conventions

- Use server actions for mutations; keep components thin
- Validate inputs with Zod
- Prefer named exports
- No inline styles; use Tailwind
- Keep components focused; extract reusable logic to lib

## Domain Logic

- Put calculations in `lib/calculations.ts`
- Put formatters in `lib/formatters.ts`
- Put validators in `lib/validators.ts`
- Put types in `lib/types.ts`
